<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0160">
<l>neṭiyataṉ muṉṉa roṟṟumey keṭutaluṅ</l>
<l>kuṟiyataṉ muṉṉart taṉṉuru viraṭṭalu</l>
<l>maṟiyat tōṉṟiya neṟiyiya leṉpa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The consonant which follows long vowels is dropped,</l>
<l>and [that which follows] short vowels</l>
<l>has its shape doubled ;</l>
<l>they say that in order to know [these conditions],</l>
<l>a system of prescribed rules [was] revealed.<note place="foot">E.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">kōl + tītu &gt; kōṟītu, kōl + naṉṟu &gt; kōṉaṉṟu, tāṉ + nallaṉ &gt; tāṉallaṉ;</foreign> but <foreign xml:lang="ta">maṇ + akal &gt; maṇṇakal, poṉ + akal &gt; poṉṉakal.</foreign></note></l>
<l>thus it is said.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
